headline: Macro Headwind-Immune CVS Health Stock Set to Extend 50% YTD Rally
summary: CVS Health (CVS) is a top S&P 500 performer in 2025, with year-to-date returns exceeding 50%. Moreover, the stock has shirked off Trump-mania, tariff levies, and a global trade war like water off a duck’s back. headline: This S&P 500 Stock Soared While the Market Plunged. Is It Still a Buy Now?
summary: Roughly four out of five S&P 500 (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) stocks are in negative territory in 2025.  Most of those stocks weren't immune to the meltdown that occurred in recent days following President Trump's "Liberation Day" announcement of steep reciprocal tariffs.  At least one S&P 500 stock soared as the market plunged.

headline: UnitedHealth Group (NYSE:UNH) Climbs 20% In One Month
summary: UnitedHealth Group (NYSE:UNH) saw its share price rise by 20% over the last month, a significant move against the backdrop of the broader market's recent volatility. While no specific events related directly to UnitedHealth could be isolated as a catalyst, the market's overall fluctuations highlighted by the recent 3,000-point jump in the Dow Jones and a 12% increase in the Nasdaq may have provided a supportive environment.
